= Mandelbrot3D =
#context: vop
#type: node

"""Computes a 3D Mandelbulb fractal value at a given position."""

== Overview ==

Mandelbrot3D evaluates the Mandelbulb fractal formula at position P and returns a normalized escape-time value. Use the output to drive density, color, or displacement in volume and surface shaders.

References:
- [Entagma - VEX in Houdini: Mandelbrot and Mandelbulb|https://vimeo.com/176911687]
- [Zeus VFX - 3D Fractal in Houdini Tutorial|https://youtu.be/-qgtQ91oItQ]

@parameters

P:
    #id: P
    Sample position in 3D space.

phase:
    #id: phase
    Phase offset added to the fractal iteration. Animating this value morphs the fractal shape over time.

N:
    #id: N
    Power exponent for the Mandelbulb formula. Default is `8`. Higher values produce sharper, more detailed bulbs.

maxIter:
    #id: maxIter
    Maximum number of iterations. Higher values increase detail at the cost of performance.

@outputs

value:
    Normalized escape-time value in [0, 1]. Points inside the set return `0`.
